Mix balance — the melody is the LEAD VOICE and must be the most prominent element:
- Melody: amp 1.0-1.5 — loudest, clearly audible as the part listeners can hum along to.
- Harmony: amp 0.3-0.6 — sits below the melody, providing support without competing.
- Percussion: amp 0.5-0.8 for kicks, lower for other hits — provides rhythmic foundation without overpowering.
If the input parts have amplitudes that violate this balance, adjust them so the melody is always on top.

